      {
        "title": "2. `filters.py` — `match`, `filter_jobs`",
        "content": "\n**Gaps:** word-boundary regex false-positive/negative (e.g. `include=[\"ai\"]` shouldn't match \"email\" but should match \"AI Engineer\"), exclude taking priority over include, empty rule sets returning True (no filters = pass-through), case-insensitive location substring match, cutoff behavior on unparseable `posted_at` (must be *kept*, per the comment), `max_age_days` as a float string.\n\n```python\nfrom datetime import datetime, timedelta, timezone\nfrom filters import match, filter_jobs\nfrom models import Job\n\ndef job(**kw):\n    return Job(source=\"s\", company=\"c\", external_id=\"1\", title=\"Backend Engineer\",\n               url=\"u\", location=\"Remote, USA\", department=\"Eng\", **kw)\n\ndef test_exclude_wins_over_include():\n    j = job(title=\"Staff AI Engineer (Contract)\")\n    assert match(j, include=[\"engineer\"], exclude=[\"contract\"]) is False\n\ndef test_include_word_boundary_no_substring_match():\n    j = job(title=\"Email Marketing Specialist\")\n    assert match(j, include=[\"ai\"]) is False   # \"ai\" inside \"Email\" must NOT match\n\ndef test_no_rules_passes():\n    assert match(job()) is True\n\ndef test_location_case_insensitive_substring():\n    assert match(job(location=\"Seattle, WA\"), locations=[\"seattle\"]) is True\n\ndef test_cutoff_keeps_unparseable_posted_at():\n    j = job(posted_at=\"garbage\")\n    cutoff = datetime.now(timezone.utc) - timedelta(days=1)\n    assert match(j, cutoff=cutoff) is True\n\ndef test_cutoff_drops_stale_parseable_posted_at():\n    j = job(posted_at=(datetime.now(timezone.utc) - timedelta(days=30)).isoformat())\n    cutoff = datetime.now(timezone.utc) - timedelta(days=7)\n    assert match(j, cutoff=cutoff) is False\n\ndef test_filter_jobs_max_age_days_builds_cutoff():\n    old = job(posted_at=(datetime.now(timezone.utc) - timedelta(days=10)).isoformat())\n    new = job(posted_at=datetime.now(timezone.utc).isoformat())\n    out = filter_jobs([old, new], {\"max_age_days\": 1})\n    assert out == [new]\n```\n\n---\n\n",
