        "title": "6b. Bespoke HTML/blob parsers — the riskiest untested code in the repo",
        "content": "\n- `_balanced_json` — no test for unbalanced braces, braces inside strings (`\"{\"`), escaped quotes, `start` past a `{` that never closes → returns `None`.\n- `_extract_ds1` (Google) — primary regex vs. fallback regex, malformed JSON, `data[0]` not a list.\n- `_apple_hydration` — `JSON.parse(\"...\")` double-decode with escaped quotes inside the JS string, missing marker, truncated blob.\n- `_apple_posted_at` — nanosecond truncation regex, missing/garbage input.\n- `parse_deshaw` — dedup via `seen`, missing title/id skip, `unescape()` of HTML entities, missing href fallback.\n- `parse_twosigma` — triplicate-anchor dedup, location lookup bounded to `[m.end(), next_anchor.start())`, last-card `+800` char fallback window.\n- `_bd_location` — parent-chain walk, `None`/non-dict termination.\n\n```python\nfrom fetchers import _balanced_json, _extract_ds1, _apple_hydration, _apple_posted_at, parse_deshaw, parse_twosigma, _bd_location\n\ndef test_balanced_json_handles_braces_in_strings():\n    text = '{\"a\": \"value with } brace\", \"b\": 1}'\n    assert _balanced_json(text, 0) == text\n\ndef test_balanced_json_unterminated_returns_none():\n    assert _balanced_json('{\"a\": 1', 0) is None\n\ndef test_extract_ds1_primary_pattern():\n    html = \"AF_initDataCallback({key: 'ds:1', hash:'1', data:[[[\\\"id1\\\"]]] , sideChannel:{}});\"\n    assert _extract_ds1(html) == [[\"id1\"]]\n\ndef test_extract_ds1_malformed_json_returns_empty():\n    html = \"key: 'ds:1', data:[not json], sideChannel:{}\"\n    assert _extract_ds1(html) == []\n\ndef test_apple_posted_at_truncates_nanoseconds():\n    assert _apple_posted_at(\"2024-01-01T00:00:03.812668311Z\") == \"2024-01-01T00:00:03.812668+00:00\"\n\ndef test_apple_posted_at_empty_input():\n    assert _apple_posted_at(\"\") == \"\"\n\ndef test_parse_deshaw_dedupes_by_job_id():\n    html = ('<div data-job-id=\"1\"><span class=\"job-display-name\">SWE</span>'\n            '<span class=\"location\">NYC</span></div>' * 2)\n    assert len(parse_deshaw(\"deshaw\", html)) == 1\n\ndef test_parse_twosigma_dedupes_triplicate_anchors():\n    html = ('<a href=\"https://careers.twosigma.com/careers/JobDetail/x/123\">Role</a>'\n            '<div class=\"article__header__content__text\"><span>NYC</span></div>') * 3\n    assert len(parse_twosigma(\"twosigma\", html)) == 1\n\ndef test_bd_location_walks_parent_chain():\n    city = {\"en_name\": \"SF\", \"parent\": {\"en_name\": \"CA\", \"parent\": {\"en_name\": \"US\", \"parent\": None}}}\n    assert _bd_location(city) == \"SF, CA, US\"\n\ndef test_bd_location_none_returns_empty():\n    assert _bd_location(None) == \"\"\n```\n\n",
